    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "I think the right approach is thinking about what we want to achieve first.\r\n\r\n1. Do we want to require anyone making any changes to this codebase to publish those changes again, no matter what? AGPL\r\n2. Do we want to require them to publish changes only if they distribute them? LGPL\r\n3. Do we want to allow anyone doing anything with it, even without contributing back? MIT\r\n\r\nI lean towards 1 - anyone can run it and redistribute, but any changes have to be made public under the same license again.",
